{
    "chapter": 80,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "80:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>He, the Prophet, frowned, glowered with his face, and turned away,</p>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "80:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>because the blind man came to him: `Abd Allh son of Umm Maktm, who interrupted him while he was busy with those notables of Quryash whose submission [to God] he was very eager for. The blind man was not aware that he was busy with these and so he called out to him, `Teach me of what God has taught you'. However, the Prophet (s) went off to his house. He was then reproached for this with what was revealed in this sra. Afterwards, whenever he came to him, the Prophet would say to him, `Greetings to him on whose account God reproached me!', and would lay down his cloak for him.</p>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "80:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And how would you know? Perhaps he would cleanse himself (yazzakk: the original t' [of yatazakk] has been assimilated with the zy), that is, [perhaps] he would purge himself of sins by what he hears from you,</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "80:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>or be admonished (yadhdhakkar: the original t' [of yatadhakkar] has been assimilated with the dhl) and so the reminder, the admonition heard from you, might benefit him (a variant reading [for tanfa`uhu] has tanfa`ahu as the response to the optative statement).</p>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "80:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>But as for the one [who thinks himself] self-sufficient, through wealth,</p>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "80:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>to him you [do] attend (tasadd: a variant reading has tassadd, where the original second t' [of tatasadd] has been assimilated with the sd), [him] you accept and turn your attention to;</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "80:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>yet it is not your concern if he does not cleanse himself, [if he does not] believe.</p>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "80:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>But as for him who comes to you hurrying (yas` is a circumstantial qualifier referring to the subject of [the verb] j'a, `comes')</p>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "80:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>fearful, of God (wa-huwa yakhsh is a circumstantial qualifier referring to the subject of [the verb] yas`, `hurrying') — this being the blind man —</p>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "80:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>to him you pay no heed (talahh: the original second t' [of tatalahh] has been omitted), that is to say, from him you are distracted [by other things].</p>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "80:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>No indeed!, do not behave like this. Truly it, the sra, is, or the verses [are], a reminder, an admonition for [all] creatures —</p>"
        },
        "12": {
            "verses": {
                "80:12": {
                    "id": 12
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>so let whoever will, remember it, preserve it [in his memory] and thus be admonished by it —</p>"
        },
        "13": {
            "verses": {
                "80:13": {
                    "id": 13
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>on leaves (f suhufin is the second predicate of innah, `truly it', and what precedes it is a parenthetical statement) [that are] honoured, by God,</p>"
        },
        "14": {
            "verses": {
                "80:14": {
                    "id": 14
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>elevated, in the heavens, purified, exalted above the touch of devils,</p>"
        },
        "15": {
            "verses": {
                "80:15": {
                    "id": 15
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>in the hands of scribes, who write it down from the Preserved Tablet,</p>"
        },
        "16": {
            "verses": {
                "80:16": {
                    "id": 16
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>noble, pious, obedient to God, exalted be He: these being the angels.</p>"
        },
        "17": {
            "verses": {
                "80:17": {
                    "id": 17
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Perish man!, accursed be the disbeliever! What has made him ungrateful? (an interrogative statement meant as a rebuke) — what has driven him to disbelief?</p>"
        },
        "18": {
            "verses": {
                "80:18": {
                    "id": 18
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>From what thing has He created him? (an interrogative meant as an affirmative, which He then explains by saying):</h2>"
        },
        "19": {
            "verses": {
                "80:19": {
                    "id": 19
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>From a drop of sperm did He create him then proportion him, [in stages] as a blood-clot, then an embryo up to the last [stage] of his creation.</p>"
        },
        "20": {
            "verses": {
                "80:20": {
                    "id": 20
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Then He made the way, his exit from his mother's belly, easy for him;</p>"
        },
        "21": {
            "verses": {
                "80:21": {
                    "id": 21
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>then He makes him die and buries him, He places him in a grave that hides him;</p>"
        },
        "22": {
            "verses": {
                "80:22": {
                    "id": 22
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>then, when He wills, He will raise him, for the Resurrection.</p>"
        },
        "23": {
            "verses": {
                "80:23": {
                    "id": 23
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>No indeed! Verily, he has not accomplished, he has not done, what He, his Lord, commanded him, to [do].</p>"
        },
        "24": {
            "verses": {
                "80:24": {
                    "id": 24
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>So let man consider, in reflection, his [source of] food, how it is determined and procured for him:</h2>"
        },
        "25": {
            "verses": {
                "80:25": {
                    "id": 25
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>that We pour down water, from the clouds, plenteously;</h2>"
        },
        "26": {
            "verses": {
                "80:26": {
                    "id": 26
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>then We split the earth into fissures, with vegetation,</h2>"
        },
        "27": {
            "verses": {
                "80:27": {
                    "id": 27
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and cause the grains, such as wheat and barley, to grow therein,</p>"
        },
        "28": {
            "verses": {
                "80:28": {
                    "id": 28
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and vines and herbs (qadb is moist qatt),</h2>"
        },
        "29": {
            "verses": {
                "80:29": {
                    "id": 29
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and olives and date-palms,</h2>"
        },
        "30": {
            "verses": {
                "80:30": {
                    "id": 30
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and gardens of dense foliage, orchards teeming with trees,</h2>"
        },
        "31": {
            "verses": {
                "80:31": {
                    "id": 31
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and fruits and pastures (abb is what cattle graze; it is also said to be `straw'),</p>"
        },
        "32": {
            "verses": {
                "80:32": {
                    "id": 32
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>as sustenance (understand mat`an as mut`atan or tamt`an, as explained above in the previous sra) for you and your flocks (also as [explained] above).</p>"
        },
        "33": {
            "verses": {
                "80:33": {
                    "id": 33
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>So when the [deafening] Cry, the second blast, comes —</h2>"
        },
        "34": {
            "verses": {
                "80:34": {
                    "id": 34
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>the day when a man will flee from his [own] brother,</h2>"
        },
        "35": {
            "verses": {
                "80:35": {
                    "id": 35
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and his mother and his father,</h2>"
        },
        "36": {
            "verses": {
                "80:36": {
                    "id": 36
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and his wife and his sons (yawma, `the day [when]', is a substitution for idh, `when', the response to which is indicated by [what follows]) —</p>"
        },
        "37": {
            "verses": {
                "80:37": {
                    "id": 37
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>every person that day will have a matter to preoccupy him, a predicament to distract him from the affairs of others, in other words, every person will be preoccupied with his own self.</p>"
        },
        "38": {
            "verses": {
                "80:38": {
                    "id": 38
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>On that day some faces will be shining, radiant,</h2>"
        },
        "39": {
            "verses": {
                "80:39": {
                    "id": 39
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>laughing, joyous, happy — these are the believers.</h2>"
        },
        "40": {
            "verses": {
                "80:40": {
                    "id": 40
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>And some faces on that day will be covered with dust,</h2>"
        },
        "41": {
            "verses": {
                "80:41": {
                    "id": 41
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>overcast, covered, with gloom, darkness and blackness.</h2>"
        },
        "42": {
            "verses": {
                "80:42": {
                    "id": 42
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Those, the people of this predicament, are the disbelievers, the profligates, those who have combined disbelief with profligacy. Meccan, consisting of 29 verses.</p>"
        }
    }
}